summary: CD Projekt Red explains controversial Cyberpunk in-game ad featuring trans model
title: CD Projekt Red explains controversial Cyberpunk in-game ad featuring trans model
excerpt: What a hypersexualized in-fiction ad reveals about the highly anticipated RPG
description: Okay so the only things I’ve seen about the in game ad that people are calling transphobic on tumblr are either text posts that give zero context and a link to a screenshot on twitter that also doesn’t give any context so I decided to look it up for myself before making any judgement and while everyone is free to criticize it as I do agree that it could have been handled much better, I do also believe that people are over reacting and that CD Projekt Red is at least trying to be inclusive towards trans/non binary people and that the intention of the ad and others like it are which are intended to be something that players were supposed to fight against as they represent the hyper aggressive nature of over-sexualized marketing makes sense. That being said if mishaps like this keep happening then yeah I can def understand a public outrage but for now as a trans person it doesn’t bother me personally as the developers have previously stated that players can have a gnc/trans playable character as well as full frontal nudity so having this kind of content was expected, but the intention of this post was to spread context so if you read the article and are still mad then thats fine, again the situation could have been handled better.

cyberpunk genre commentary: corporations are parasites and one of the ways they subjugate The Masses is by controlling information flow. physical augmentations in our fictional world is a direct analogy for our growing reliance on tech owned by these corporations, who thereby own the data output by these devices/services -
